{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295/events","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295","id":1069346302,"node_id":"I_kwDOABkWpM4_vO3-","number":43295,"title":"`iterate` on `SubArray` uses slow default fallback","user":{"login":"jakobnissen","id":23193950,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTkzOTUw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23193950?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen","html_url":"https://github.com/jakobnissen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakobnissen/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":232418,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyMzI0MTg=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/help%20wanted","name":"help wanted","color":"0b02e1","default":true,"description":"Indicates that a maintainer wants help on an issue or pull request"},{"id":62693664,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw2MjY5MzY2NA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/labels/arrays","name":"arrays","color":"006b75","default":false,"description":"[a, r, r, a, y, s]"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":5,"created_at":"2021-12-02T09:55:26Z","updated_at":"2023-02-24T13:35:22Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"It turns out the default fallback is actually rather slow for `SubArray`:
```
julia> using BenchmarkTools

julia> f(v) = sum((i for i in v), init=0);

julia> v = rand(Int, 2^12);

julia> @btime f(v);
  248.161 ns (1 allocation: 16 bytes)

julia> @btime f($(view(v, 1:2^12)));
  2.109 μs (0 allocations: 0 bytes)

julia> g(v) = sum((@inbounds v[i] for i in eachindex(v)), init=0);

julia> @btime g($(view(v, 1:2^12)));
  228.657 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)
```
I think this is rather bad as `SubArray` is a fairly fundamental type, and people tend to use it specifically when they are looking for performance.

It appears to be the boundschecking that is particularly expensive for `SubArray`. #42030 is related to this, but even if it is decided that default implementations should not use `@inbounds`, this should still be solved by creating a specialized method for `SubArray`.

This occurs on Julia 1.6.3, 1.7.0 and master as of 2021-12-02.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295/reactions","total_count":4,"+1":4,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1443690722","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295#issuecomment-1443690722","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/43295","id":1443690722,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5WDPji","user":{"login":"matthias314","id":56549971,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2NTQ5OTcx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/56549971?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314","html_url":"https://github.com/matthias314","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/matthias314/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-02-24T13:35:22Z","updated_at":"2023-02-24T13:35:22Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I've started a discussion in  #48773 to gauge the support for an approach based on `@propagate_inbounds` for `iterate`. Let's see what it gives.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1443690722/reactions","tot